 <h3>Exponentiation and the remainder operators must be without a unit. Therefore we need to define an unitless matrix</h3>
 <p>
  <span class="eq">
   <b>
    <var>matrix</var>
   </b>
   <sub>unitless</sub>
   =
   <span class="matrix">
    <span class="tr">
     <span class="td">
     </span>
     <span class="td">9</span>
     <span class="td">
     </span>
    </span>
    <span class="tr">
     <span class="td">
     </span>
     <span class="td">-4</span>
     <span class="td">
     </span>
    </span>
    <span class="tr">
     <span class="td">
     </span>
     <span class="td">3.14</span>
     <span class="td">
     </span>
    </span>
    <span class="tr">
     <span class="td">
     </span>
     <span class="td">-7</span>
     <span class="td">
     </span>
    </span>
    <span class="tr">
     <span class="td">
     </span>
     <span class="td">8.88</span>
     <span class="td">
     </span>
    </span>
   </span>
  </span>
 </p>
 <p>
  <span class="eq">
   <var>f</var>
   (
   <var>m1</var>
   ;
   <var>matrix</var>
